South East Governors will meet in Owerri, the Imo State capital to deliberate on security- related issues today. Also expected at the meeting are the Brigade Commanders, Navy, Air Force Commanders, Inspector General of Police, Ohanaeze Ndigbo and other stakeholders. The Governors, according to sources, are meeting to find solution to the recent insecurity challenges facing the zone, particularly the recent jail break and attack on Imo Police headquarters that led to release of over 600 suspects in police custody and 1,881 inmates at the Correctional Service Centre Owerri. Chief Press Secretary to Imo Governor, Oguike Nwachuku confirmed the meeting. He said the governors would brief the media after the meeting. Details shortlyâ€¦